			<div class="content" id="post-content-4535023">
									

<p>Probably my only issue with this guide is that it treats the two linking methods (<em>i.e.</em> <strong>[URL link name]</strong> vs <strong><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[[URL&#32;|&#32;link&#32;name]]]</span></strong>) like they're the same. If you're linking on-site, the latter is preferable, because it allows the Backlinks to function properly and provides more visibility to your article. Also, as someone who's forced to use scp-wiki.wikidot.com on their phone, it's an annoyance to click on a link and then manually correct the URL to view the site.</p>
<p>Could a clarification be made in this guide to emphasize that the triple-bracket method is preferred?</p>

